TITLE: Deleting Row Ranges in Accumulo
DESCRIPTION: The deleterows command removes a range of rows from a table. Note that the start row is exclusive while the end row is inclusive in the deletion range.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/accumulo-website/blob/main/1.4/user_manual/Shell_Commands.md#2025-04-11_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
usage: deleterows [-?] [-b <arg>] [-e <arg>] [-f] [-t <table>]   
description: delete a range of rows in a table.  Note that rows matching the start   
          row ARE NOT deleted, but rows matching the end row ARE deleted.   
  -?,-help  display this help   
  -b,-begin-row <arg>  begin row   
  -e,-end-row <arg>  end row   
  -f,-force  delete data even if start or end are not specified   
  -t,-tableName <table>  table to delete row range
```

