TITLE: Memory Usage Monitoring Shell Script
DESCRIPTION: Bash script that monitors the Resident Set Size (RSS) of a specified process ID, collecting memory usage data every 5 seconds for up to an hour. Data is written to output_mem_usage.log for subsequent analysis.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/accumulo-website/blob/main/_posts/blog/2024-04-09-does-a-compactor-return-memory-to-OS.md#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
#!/bin/bash 
PID=$1 
echo "Tracking PID: $PID" 
DURATION=3600 # for 1 hour 
INTERVAL=5    # every 5 seconds 
rm output_mem_usage.log 

while [ $DURATION -gt 0 ]; do 
    ps -o %mem,rss -p $PID | tail -n +2 >> output_mem_usage.log 
    sleep $INTERVAL 
    DURATION=$((DURATION - INTERVAL)) 
done
```

